849
00:48:45,184 --> 00:48:46,344
I'm sorry.

850
00:48:47,014 --> 00:48:50,855
I would like to apologize to you and your family.

851
00:48:51,554 --> 00:48:53,954
Please forget everything...

852
00:48:54,525 --> 00:48:55,824
they told you.

853
00:48:59,625 --> 00:49:01,594
Well, sir.

854
00:49:03,335 --> 00:49:04,434
Yes?

855
00:49:08,135 --> 00:49:09,275
Woo Ri.

856
00:49:11,105 --> 00:49:12,405
This way. Let's go.

857
00:49:48,574 --> 00:49:50,114
Goodness.

858
00:49:52,684 --> 00:49:53,855
Did it go well?

859
00:49:53,954 --> 00:49:55,454
You said it was a simple procedure.

860
00:49:56,284 --> 00:49:57,324
What?

861
00:49:57,925 --> 00:49:59,755
- Ma'am. - Mother.

862
00:50:00,385 --> 00:50:02,255
- Are you all right? - Are you okay?

863
00:50:05,224 --> 00:50:06,795
- Be careful. - I can't believe this.

864
00:50:24,914 --> 00:50:29,054
My mother had me as a teenager when she was still in school.

865
00:50:30,885 --> 00:50:32,755
Even I don't know what to do at the age of 29.

866
00:50:33,355 --> 00:50:35,625
She must have had a lot on her mind.

867
00:50:37,094 --> 00:50:38,625
How scared she must have been.

868
00:50:40,664 --> 00:50:45,065
But she must have had a reason when she decided to have me.

869
00:50:46,204 --> 00:50:48,675
There must be a reason why I'm in this world...

870
00:50:49,875 --> 00:50:53,405
and why something like this happened to me too.

871
00:50:54,875 --> 00:50:56,275
There must be a reason for that.

872
00:51:06,925 --> 00:51:08,324
She's still not answering her phone.

873
00:51:09,855 --> 00:51:11,594
Where did she go?

874
00:51:13,795 --> 00:51:15,764
Woo Ri. Where have you been?

875
00:51:16,235 --> 00:51:17,505
Why didn't you go through with the surgery?

876
00:51:17,804 --> 00:51:19,104
Woo Ri.

877
00:51:19,105 --> 00:51:21,175
You're not considering their offer, right?

878
00:51:21,405 --> 00:51:24,244
Don't give a thought to what those jerks said.

879
00:51:25,744 --> 00:51:27,005
Mom.

880
00:51:27,275 --> 00:51:29,215
Grandma. Kang Jae.

881
00:51:30,175 --> 00:51:31,315
I'm going to...

882
00:51:32,244 --> 00:51:33,514
have this baby.

883
00:51:38,184 --> 00:51:39,954
What do you mean? Why would you?

884
00:51:40,355 --> 00:51:42,054
You were a victim of a medical accident.

885
00:51:42,394 --> 00:51:44,425
This is the same as getting infected at the hospital.

886
00:51:45,025 --> 00:51:46,224
Then what about me?

887
00:51:46,894 --> 00:51:48,034
Was I an accident too?

888
00:51:48,565 --> 00:51:49,735
Was I an infection?

889
00:51:51,005 --> 00:51:52,163
What?

890
00:51:52,164 --> 00:51:53,704
Why did you have me?

891
00:51:54,875 --> 00:51:56,275
Do you regret having me?

892
00:51:56,835 --> 00:51:59,104
What are you talking about? Why would I regret having you?

893
00:51:59,105 --> 00:52:00,175
Mom.

894
00:52:00,715 --> 00:52:02,244
When I was in middle school,

895
00:52:03,114 --> 00:52:04,444
I heard you say...

896
00:52:04,445 --> 00:52:06,045
you shouldn't have given birth to me.

897
00:52:06,644 --> 00:52:08,355
You couldn't be a singer because of me.

898
00:52:09,885 --> 00:52:13,125
What you said had scarred me my entire life.

899
00:52:14,724 --> 00:52:16,025
It didn't go away.

900
00:52:17,324 --> 00:52:19,025
I was a burden to you.

901
00:52:21,195 --> 00:52:23,394
I didn't want people to look down on me.

902
00:52:23,965 --> 00:52:26,164
I didn't want to make even a single mistake.

903
00:52:27,105 --> 00:52:29,005
That's why I pledged to abstain.

904
00:52:30,474 --> 00:52:31,644
Woo Ri.

905
00:52:32,844 --> 00:52:34,114
I thought...

906
00:52:35,514 --> 00:52:37,243
you went through with the pledge...

907
00:52:37,244 --> 00:52:39,085
because you were embarrassed that I had you at 16.

908
00:52:40,144 --> 00:52:42,655
I never thought I couldn't be a singer because of you.

909
00:52:43,614 --> 00:52:45,654
I wanted to be a successful singer...

910
00:52:45,655 --> 00:52:48,454
because I wanted to be a mom you could be proud of.

911
00:52:49,954 --> 00:52:52,494
I don't care what my job is. I have you.

912
00:52:53,795 --> 00:52:55,434
There were so many moments...

913
00:52:56,264 --> 00:52:58,704
you made me happy ever since you were born.

914
00:53:01,275 --> 00:53:04,905
It's quite the opposite. I always felt bad for you.

915
00:53:05,945 --> 00:53:07,914
The thing you tell me the most is...

916
00:53:08,914 --> 00:53:12,885
"Mom, why do you live like that?"

917
00:53:14,554 --> 00:53:16,085
I'm not good at anything.

918
00:53:16,715 --> 00:53:18,084
I always cause trouble.

919
00:53:18,085 --> 00:53:19,985
I'm far from being a perfect mother.

920
00:53:21,454 --> 00:53:23,425
You're embarrassed of me.

921
00:53:26,594 --> 00:53:28,195
No, Mom.

922
00:53:29,394 --> 00:53:31,465
Why would I be embarrassed of you?

923
00:53:37,545 --> 00:53:39,344
I'm so proud...

924
00:53:39,974 --> 00:53:42,974
that you are working so hard to achieve your dream.

925
00:53:45,184 --> 00:53:46,885
You're my mom.

926
00:53:47,655 --> 00:53:49,914
You brought me into this world.

927
00:53:51,954 --> 00:53:55,594
I wouldn't trade you for anything in the world.

928
00:54:05,605 --> 00:54:09,105
You just healed the scar in my heart.

929
00:54:10,474 --> 00:54:12,644
You don't have to tell me why you decided to keep me.

930
00:54:13,574 --> 00:54:15,445
I know why.

931
00:54:17,045 --> 00:54:18,885
I'm the reason why.

932
00:54:20,985 --> 00:54:22,114
Woo Ri.

933
00:54:30,925 --> 00:54:32,025
Mom.

934
00:54:34,164 --> 00:54:36,295
You gave me a chance.

935
00:54:37,335 --> 00:54:39,764
So I'm loved by so many people in my life.

936
00:54:42,704 --> 00:54:46,644
Now, I want to give a chance to this baby.

937
00:54:52,715 --> 00:54:54,045
Why you?

938
00:54:55,585 --> 00:54:57,355
Why did this happen to you?

939
00:55:14,574 --> 00:55:16,335
Do you think having a baby is easy?

940
00:55:16,605 --> 00:55:17,804
You think it will just come to you?

941
00:55:18,175 --> 00:55:19,843
It's a huge responsibility.

942
00:55:19,844 --> 00:55:22,315
I know that too. I'm ready for it.

943
00:55:23,244 --> 00:55:24,843
When your mother told me...

944
00:55:24,844 --> 00:55:28,215
she was pregnant 30 years ago, I didn't think about anything.

945
00:55:28,784 --> 00:55:32,084
A 16-year-old girl was pregnant. I told her to get rid of it.

946
00:55:32,085 --> 00:55:35,094
I dragged her to the hospital to get an abortion right away.

947
00:55:35,795 --> 00:55:39,264
But your mother ran away.

948
00:55:40,594 --> 00:55:42,635
She's a good runner.

949
00:55:42,835 --> 00:55:44,864
If she wasn't a good runner,

950
00:55:48,304 --> 00:55:51,275
it would have been a huge problem.

951
00:55:52,204 --> 00:55:56,114
I don't know why I was so against it back then.

952
00:55:56,675 --> 00:56:00,244
I prayed and repented all my life.

953
00:56:03,614 --> 00:56:07,054
But you and your mother are in different shoes.

954
00:56:07,255 --> 00:56:09,124
You didn't do anything.

955
00:56:09,125 --> 00:56:11,524
You didn't do anything that requires you to be responsible.

956
00:56:11,525 --> 00:56:12,724
I know that.

957
00:56:13,025 --> 00:56:17,363
But still. I have a chance to bring a baby into this world.

958
00:56:17,364 --> 00:56:19,534
You have a very beautiful, generous heart.

959
00:56:20,235 --> 00:56:23,335
But still. Why must you do it?

960
00:56:24,105 --> 00:56:27,444
Grandma. If Mary's grandma was against it,

961
00:56:27,445 --> 00:56:29,073
Jesus wouldn't have been born.

962
00:56:29,074 --> 00:56:32,084
You're not Virgin Mary. Will you give birth to Jesus?

963
00:56:32,085 --> 00:56:33,744
That's my religious name too.

964
00:56:34,454 --> 00:56:36,114
You gave that name to me.

965
00:56:37,054 --> 00:56:39,184
Goodness. Oh, no.

966
00:56:39,684 --> 00:56:40,954
Oh, no.

967
00:56:49,034 --> 00:56:50,364
- Gosh. - We'll be okay.

968
00:56:52,804 --> 00:56:55,534
(Seo Gwi Nyeo's Pork Cutlet)

969
00:57:05,844 --> 00:57:07,144
Must you have this baby?

970
00:57:12,925 --> 00:57:14,295
I'm sorry.

971
00:57:19,565 --> 00:57:23,534
I know that my decision right now is very unrealistic.

972
00:57:25,364 --> 00:57:28,034
Just ask anyone on the street.

973
00:57:29,074 --> 00:57:30,574
They will say I'm crazy.

974
00:57:32,545 --> 00:57:33,605
Right.

975
00:57:34,945 --> 00:57:36,875
To be honest, it's not easy for me either.

976
00:57:38,644 --> 00:57:40,985
Even my family can't understand me.

977
00:57:42,184 --> 00:57:44,724
I won't ask you to understand my decision.

978
00:57:53,324 --> 00:57:56,135
I'm sorry for making a selfish decision.

979
00:58:00,364 --> 00:58:02,473
But I don't have the right to stop you...

980
00:58:02,474 --> 00:58:04,275
from making that decision.

981
00:58:05,775 --> 00:58:06,945
I'll just...

982
00:58:08,344 --> 00:58:11,385
I'll just help you make a wise decision.

983
00:58:16,014 --> 00:58:17,085
Kang Jae.

984
00:58:28,094 --> 00:58:29,195
Woo Ri.

985
00:58:30,335 --> 00:58:31,465
It's okay.

986
00:58:32,764 --> 00:58:34,105
I'm sorry.

987
00:58:36,375 --> 00:58:37,375
Yes!

988
00:58:48,985 --> 00:58:50,985
- Hello? - Ms. Oh?

989
00:58:51,554 --> 00:58:52,824
This is Raphael.

990
00:58:53,355 --> 00:58:54,954
Hello.

991
00:58:56,925 --> 00:58:58,323
What's this about?

992
00:58:58,324 --> 00:59:00,425
